ACS Wins Contract to Build 500-Megawatt Power Station in Brazil

-- B y   B e n   S i l l s
-- 
2011-08-19T11:28:13Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-19/acs-wins-contract-to-build-500-megawatt-power-station-in-brazil.html
Actividades de Construccion y
Servicios SA’s Initec Energia unit won a contract to build a
500-megawatt combined-cycle gas-fired power plant for  MPX
Energia SA. (MPXE3)   The plant will be located in Maranhao state in the interior
of the country about 1,000 miles (1,600 kilometers) north of the
national capital Brasilia and is due to enter  service  by
February 2014, the company said today in an e-mailed statement.  The contract is worth about 260 million euros ($371
million), El Economista reported earlier today. Initec didn’t
say how much the project will cost.  Initec is a wholly owned subsidiary of ACS that builds
power plants.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ben Sills in Madrid at   bsills@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Reed Landberg at   landberg@bloomberg.net  